headline: Kevin O'Leary Says His $12.9M Trading Card Belongs With Fine Art. To Him, It's 'No Different' From Warhol And Pollock
summary: Kevin O’Leary just dropped nearly $13 million on what some might dismiss as just a trading card. But to him, it’s in the same league as fine art—no different from owning an original Warhol or Pollock. The investor and television personality known as “Mr. Wonderful” teamed up with two partners last month to buy a one-of-a-kind sports card signed by NBA Hall of Famers Michael Jordan and Kobe Bryant for $12.9 million.
